Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop
them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add
the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if
necessary.

> Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some
> nice colour.

Once cooked, transfer the sweetcorn to a #small bowl{}. Give the frying pan a
quick wipe clean.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} into the (now empty) frying pan on high heat. Once
hot, add @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} to the pan and cook until
browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once golden, add the sliced pepper to the
pan and stir-fry, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then stir in the garlic. Stir-fry for
~{1%minute}.

Add in the black beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and
@water{50%milliliters} (see pantry for amount). Bring to the boil, then lower
the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Zesty Soured Cream ==

While the fajita mix cooks, in a small bowl, combine the @soured cream{75%grams}
and lime zest.

== Assembly ==

When the fajita mix is ready, stir through the @chipotle paste{20%grams}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @BBQ sauce{32%grams} and squeeze in
some lime juice.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's
a little too thick.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your plates and top with the
chicken fajita mix.

Top with the charred corn and scatter over the cheese. Finish with a big
dollop of the zesty soured cream - wedges loaded!

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!